        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Updating this to just hiding the autocmd window. Can try to tackle the unnecessary redrawing of hidden windows in another PR if @bfredl agrees that's worth pursuing.\r\n\r\n> I wonder if we should graduate that flag to a 'winhide' option similar to 'winpinned'.\r\n\r\nThis props up the question of how split windows should behave with that option (probably not worth saving/restoring layout to this end). Probably fine as a nvim_open_win() flag for that reason. Out of all the flags, I think 'winfocuseable' seems most applicable to be graduated to work with both split and floats.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-29T10:31:24Z",
